A 48-year-old woman was killed in a shooting in Manenberg on Sunday.At 19:30 the woman was wounded by a stray bullet that entered her home, says police spokesperson Lieutenant Ian Bennett. Officers responded to a shooting incident in Lillian Court, Manenberg. It is alleged that the woman was struck in the head by a stray bullet after rival gangs were shooting in the area, Bennett says.It is unknown who fired the shot and no arrests have been made.Police are investigating a case of murder.V Anyone with information on this incident is urged to call the station on 021 699 9400 or CrimeStop on 08600 1011124.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.